# Authentication & Authorization Security

## JWT Security

### Backend JWT Configuration
```csharp
// Strong secret key (min 32 characters)
services.AddAuthentication(JwtBearerDefaults.AuthenticationScheme)
    .AddJwtBearer(options =>
    {
        options.TokenValidationParameters = new TokenValidationParameters
        {
            ValidateIssuer = true,
            ValidateAudience = true,
            ValidateLifetime = true,
            ValidateIssuerSigningKey = true,
            ValidIssuer = configuration["Jwt:Issuer"],
            ValidAudience = configuration["Jwt:Audience"],
            IssuerSigningKey = new SymmetricSecurityKey(
                Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(configuration["Jwt:Key"]!)),
            ClockSkew = TimeSpan.Zero  // No clock skew tolerance
        };
    });
```

### Token Expiration
- **Access Token:** 60 minutes (short-lived)
- **Refresh Token:** 30 days (long-lived, one-time use)

### Refresh Token Security
```csharp
public class RefreshToken : Entity
{
    public string TokenHash { get; set; }  // Store HASH, not plain text
    public DateTime ExpiresAt { get; set; }
    public bool IsRevoked { get; set; }
    public bool IsUsed { get; set; }  // One-time use
}

// Generate refresh token
var token = Convert.ToBase64String(RandomNumberGenerator.GetBytes(64));
var hash = BCrypt.HashPassword(token);  // Store hash

// Validate refresh token
if (!BCrypt.Verify(providedToken, storedHash))
    return Unauthorized();

if (refreshToken.IsUsed || refreshToken.IsRevoked)
    return Unauthorized();

refreshToken.IsUsed = true;  // Mark as used
```

## Password Security

### Password Hashing (BCrypt)
```csharp
public class UserPasswordService : IPasswordHasher
{
    private readonly PasswordHashingOptions _options;
    
    public string HashPassword(string password)
    {
        // BCrypt with work factor 12 (2^12 = 4096 rounds)
        return BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.HashPassword(
            password,
            workFactor: _options.WorkFactor,  // 12
            enhancedEntropy: true
        );
    }
    
    public bool VerifyPassword(string password, string hash)
    {
        return BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.Verify(password, hash);
    }
}
```

### Password Requirements
- Minimum 8 characters
- At least one uppercase letter
- At least one lowercase letter
- At least one digit
- At least one special character

## Rate Limiting

### Critical Endpoints
```csharp
builder.Services.AddRateLimiter(options =>
{
    // Login - 5 attempts per minute per IP
    options.AddFixedWindowLimiter("login-limit", limiterOptions =>
    {
        limiterOptions.PermitLimit = 5;
        limiterOptions.Window = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(1);
    });
    
    // Register - 3 per hour per IP
    options.AddFixedWindowLimiter("register-limit", limiterOptions =>
    {
        limiterOptions.PermitLimit = 3;
        limiterOptions.Window = TimeSpan.FromHours(1);
    });
    
    // Password reset - 3 per 15 minutes per IP
    options.AddFixedWindowLimiter("password-limit", limiterOptions =>
    {
        limiterOptions.PermitLimit = 3;
        limiterOptions.Window = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(15);
    });
});

[EnableRateLimiting("login-limit")]
[HttpPost("login")]
public async Task<IActionResult> Login([FromBody] LoginRequestDto dto) { ... }
```

## CORS Security

### Strict CORS Configuration
```csharp
services.AddCors(options =>
{
    options.AddPolicy("AllowAngular", policy =>
    {
        policy.WithOrigins(
            "http://localhost:4200",  // Development
            "https://rentifynow.com"  // Production
        )
        .AllowCredentials()
        .AllowAnyMethod()
        .AllowAnyHeader();
    });
});

// Apply CORS policy
app.UseCors("AllowAngular");
```

### Security Headers
```csharp
app.Use(async (ctx, next) =>
{
    ctx.Response.Headers.Append("X-Content-Type-Options", "nosniff");
    ctx.Response.Headers.Append("X-Frame-Options", "DENY");
    ctx.Response.Headers.Append("X-XSS-Protection", "0");
    ctx.Response.Headers.Append("Referrer-Policy", "no-referrer");
    ctx.Response.Headers.Append("Permissions-Policy", "geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()");
    ctx.Response.Headers.Append("Content-Security-Policy",
        "default-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none';");
    await next();
});
```

## Frontend Token Storage

### Secure Storage
```typescript
// Store tokens in localStorage (acceptable for SPAs)
// HttpOnly cookies would be more secure but complicate architecture
localStorage.setItem('authToken', accessToken);
localStorage.setItem('refreshToken', refreshToken);

// Clear tokens on logout
logout(): void {
  localStorage.removeItem('authToken');
  localStorage.removeItem('refreshToken');
  this.currentUserSubject.next(null);
  this.router.navigate(['/auth/login']);
}
```

### Token Validation
```typescript
isTokenExpired(token: string): boolean {
  try {
    const decoded = jwtDecode<{exp: number}>(token);
    return Date.now() >= decoded.exp * 1000;
  } catch {
    return true;
  }
}
```

## Authorization Patterns

### Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
```csharp
[Authorize(Roles = "PropertyManager")]
[HttpPost("properties")]
public async Task<IActionResult> CreateProperty([FromBody] CreatePropertyDto dto) { ... }
```

### Permission-Based Authorization
```csharp
public class ActiveSubscriptionHandler : AuthorizationHandler<ActiveSubscriptionRequirement>
{
    protected override async Task HandleRequirementAsync(
        AuthorizationHandlerContext context,
        ActiveSubscriptionRequirement requirement)
    {
        var userId = Guid.Parse(context.User.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)!.Value);
        var hasActiveSubscription = await subscriptionService.HasActiveSubscriptionAsync(userId);
        
        if (hasActiveSubscription)
            context.Succeed(requirement);
    }
}

[Authorize(Policy = "ActiveSubscriber")]
[HttpGet("premium-features")]
public IActionResult GetPremiumFeatures() { ... }
```

### Frontend Guards
```typescript
export const roleGuard = (allowedRoles: string[]): CanActivateFn => {
  return (route, state) => {
    const authService = inject(AuthService);
    const router = inject(Router);
    
    const userRoles = authService.getCurrentUser()?.roles || [];
    const hasRole = allowedRoles.some(role => userRoles.includes(role));
    
    if (hasRole) return true;
    
    router.navigate(['/unauthorized']);
    return false;
  };
};

// Usage in routes
{
  path: 'admin',
  canActivate: [roleGuard(['Admin'])],
  loadComponent: () => import('./admin/admin.component')
}
```

## External Auth Security

### Google OAuth Validation
```csharp
public async Task<GoogleJsonWebSignature.Payload?> ValidateGoogleTokenAsync(string idToken)
{
    try
    {
        var settings = new GoogleJsonWebSignature.ValidationSettings
        {
            Audience = new[] { _options.Google.ClientId }
        };
        
        return await GoogleJsonWebSignature.ValidateAsync(idToken, settings);
    }
    catch (InvalidJwtException)
    {
        return null;
    }
}
```

## Security Best Practices

1. **Never Store Secrets in Code:** Use Azure Key Vault
2. **Strong JWT Keys:** Minimum 32 characters, random
3. **Short Token Lifetimes:** Access tokens expire quickly
4. **One-Time Refresh Tokens:** Mark as used after refresh
5. **Rate Limiting:** Prevent brute force attacks
6. **HTTPS Only:** All production traffic over HTTPS
7. **CORS Restrictions:** Only allow trusted origins
8. **Security Headers:** Implement all security headers
9. **Password Hashing:** BCrypt with high work factor
10. **Input Validation:** Validate all user input
11. **Audit Logging:** Log all authentication attempts
12. **Token Revocation:** Support manual token revocation

**See backend architecture rules for gRPC auth patterns.**
